&lt;p&gt;Clients trust your perspective. Teams rely on your leadership, judgment, and ability to bring clarity to ambiguity. You’re collaborative, constructive, and able to work independently while supporting the people around you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’re comfortable leading product experiences, applications, websites, campaigns, brand systems, creative operations, and multidisciplinary teams. You bring modern design sensibilities, familiarity with UX/UI and accessibility best practices, and a portfolio that demonstrates sophisticated visual design and thoughtful UX thinking.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’re curious about emerging technologies, but grounded enough to separate meaningful innovation from hype. You believe AI should support creativity, exploration, and execution, not replace thoughtful creative work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You lead with curiosity, accountability, empathy and a team-first mindset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Creative Director is responsible for the overall vision, brand quality, user experience direction, and design operations strategy for Mindgrub and its portfolio of client engagements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role focuses on creative quality, digital experience direction, and the continued evolution of modern creative workflows. The Creative Director works closely with executive leadership, production, and go-to-market teams to ensure creative work is effective, scalable, and aligned with business goals.&lt;/p&gt;
