&lt;p&gt;This position will initially support multiple strategic client engagements, working alongside a Senior Product Manager to facilitate discovery, manage product backlogs, define requirements, and guide software delivery from concept through launch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate enjoys solving complex business problems, thrives in collaborative environments, and is comfortable bringing structure to ambiguous situations. They possess an owner&#39;s mindset, communicate effectively with both technical and non-technical stakeholders, and are eager to learn new industries and business domains.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mindgrub embraces modern AI-assisted ways of working. Candidates should be comfortable incorporating generative AI tools into research, analysis, documentation, backlog management, and day-to-day product delivery while applying sound judgment and maintaining high standards for quality and accuracy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position requires strong communication skills, exceptional organization, intellectual curiosity, and a passion for building software that creates meaningful business value. If you thrive at the intersection of strategy, collaboration, and execution, we&#39;d love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
